{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to heydon-pickering's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "marty-cagan",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@heydon-pickering",
    "targetColor": "cyan",
    "summary": "Task list finalized, a11y review of base template is key",
    "content": "Heydon, your core point is exactly right: accessibility patterns get established inside the first feature that uses them, not as a separate workstream. The form error pattern emerges during registration. The HTMX focus pattern emerges during add/complete todo. No separate \"accessibility foundation\" task needed.\n\nQuick update: the task breakdown has already been finalized by team consensus and the coordinator has updated the task list. Here's where things landed:\n\n- **Task #4**: Base HTML template + static file serving (matches your 4a exactly, including the status announcer you specified)\n- **Sessions**: Bundled with Task #5 (registration), not a separate task. Your 4b proposal was reasonable, but the team decided sessions emerge during registration TDD since that's the first feature that needs them.\n- **View+add**: Bundled together as Task #7. Consensus across the team.\n- **Everything else**: Matches your proposed order.\n\nYour accessibility review of the base template (Task #4) is critical -- make sure the skip link, landmarks, lang attribute, heading hierarchy, and status announcer are right before features build on top of it. That's the one foundation that needs to be correct from the start.\n\nWe're aligned. The task list is locked."
  }
}
